            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Casterton ¶ Novr13th 1878 ¶ Dear Sir ¶  ¶ Herewith I have the pleasure to forward stems &amp; leaves of the dwarf &amp; large grass tree. In accordance with your wish I have carefully noted whether the dwarf ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">78.11.13</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Clements Macan</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M1, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Xanthorrhoea caespitosa</seg> (MEL 2216020). MS annotation by M: 'Answ 18/11/78'; letter not found.</p>
               </note>Casterton<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Vic.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Novr13th 1878</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Herewith I have the pleasure to forward stems &amp; leaves of the dwarf &amp; large grass tree. In accordance with your wish I have carefully noted whether the dwarf gradually passed into the long spike, at first I thought so, attributing the stuntedness to adverse circumstances, such as cattle browsing, bush fires &amp;c. however within the last week I have been over a large tract of country &amp; observed the two kinds growing side by side with exactly the same disadvantages, I am strongly inclined to think the two varieties are distinct. The enclosed stems were all within a few feet of each other in the bunch from which I took the large one there was a stem not in bloom more than 2 ft long, hoping you have quite recovered</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I remain</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>yours very truly</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>C. A. Macan.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Governm Botanist</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
         </div>
